 \int_a^{5a}u(x)\mathrm dx=\int_0^{a}u(t)\,(1+2^{\sin(t)}+2^{\cos(t)}+2^{\sin(t)}2^{\cos(t)})\mathrm dt. 
 \int_a^{5a}u(x)\mathrm dx=a. 
 \int_{25\pi/4}^{53\pi/4}u(x)\mathrm dx=7a=7\pi/4. 
